<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-0382 </DOCNO><TEXT>The shift crews of German nuclear power plants consist of the so-calledresponsible shift personnel (shift supervisor, deputy shift supervisor,licensed reactor operator), the non-licensed reactor operators and theroundsmen. In accordance with the particularly high qualification requirements,the paper focuses on the responsible shift personnel. The typical trainingpaths for this group of persons are described. Following this, the resultsof an evaluation of personnel data and examination results are presented.In about 1980-81, the training requirements underwent a material change.This is why the evaluation of the data is restricted to the years from1982 through 1986. It is the basis of a few conclusions or recommendationsregarding the further improvement of personnel qualifications.</TEXT></DOC>